        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): preserve unknown web search records",
        "body": "## Summary\n- preserve unrelated record-valued `tools.web.search` entries during legacy web search migration\n- continue removing only positively identified legacy provider records and known migrated globals\n- add regression coverage for custom record-valued web search config next to a legacy `apiKey`\n\nFixes #83287.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n![PR 83315 before/after proof](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/giodl73-repo/openclaw/proof-artifacts/pr-83315-fresh/pr-83315/pr-83315-fix-doctor-preserve-unknown-web-search-records-before-after-proof.png)\n\nFresh deterministic proof artifacts:\n- Summary: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/giodl73-repo/openclaw/proof-artifacts/pr-83315-fresh/pr-83315/summary.txt\n- Before/source proof log: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/giodl73-repo/openclaw/proof-artifacts/pr-83315-fresh/pr-83315/before-source-proof.log\n- After/PR proof log: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/giodl73-repo/openclaw/proof-artifacts/pr-83315-fresh/pr-83315/after-pr-83315.log\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: legacy web search migration should not drop unrelated record-valued config while moving known legacy provider settings.\n- Real environment tested: WSL Ubuntu OpenClaw worktree at `/root/src/openclaw-branches/fix-legacy-web-search-preserve-records-83287`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-web-search-migrate.test.ts` and `pnpm check:changed`.\n- Evidence after fix (terminal capture):\n\n```text\nRUN  v4.1.6 /root/src/openclaw-branches/fix-legacy-web-search-preserve-records-83287\n\n✓ unit-fast  ../../src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-web-search-migrate.test.ts (3 tests) 4ms\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  3 passed (3)\n\n[check:changed] src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-web-search-migrate.test.ts: core test\n[check:changed] src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-web-search-migrate.ts: core production\nImport cycle check: 0 runtime value cycle(s).\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: a config with legacy `apiKey`, `customSearch: { endpoint, mode }`, and `openaiCodex: { enabled }` migrates the legacy key to `plugins.entries.brave.config.webSearch` while preserving both record-valued search entries.\n- What was not tested: a live doctor repair run against a real user config file.\n- Before evidence (terminal/code capture from `origin/main`):\n\n```text\nsrc/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-web-search-migrate.ts before this patch only copied modern scoped records or non-record values:\n  if (MODERN_SCOPED_WEB_SEARCH_KEYS.has(key) || !isRecord(value)) {\n    nextSearch[key] = value;\n  }\n\nAn unrelated record-valued key such as:\n  customSearch: { endpoint: \"https://search.example.test\", mode: \"strict\" }\nwas omitted from the migrated search config.\n```\n\n## Root Cause\n- Root cause: normalization treated all record-valued unknown keys as removable unless they were in a small modern allowlist.\n- Missing detection / guardrail: no regression test covered an unrelated record-valued key beside a migrated legacy provider key.\n- Contributing context: the migration needs to remove legacy provider records, but that removal condition was broader than the set of known legacy providers.\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n- Coverage level that should have caught this: unit test.\n- Target test or file: `src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-web-search-migrate.test.ts`.\n- Scenario the test should lock in: known legacy provider config is migrated while unrelated record-valued config remains under `tools.web.search`.\n- Why this is the smallest reliable guardrail: the behavior is isolated to config normalization and does not need filesystem repair plumbing.\n\n## Validation\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-web-search-migrate.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n",
